@startuml
' GLPI + iTop Integration Architecture Diagram
' Standalone PlantUML. No external includes required.

!include ../../../../tooling/styles/plantuml/interaction/sequence-diagram-style.iuml

skinparam queue {
  BackgroundColor #F3E5F5
  BorderColor #6A1B9A
}

title GLPI + iTop Integration Architecture\nITAM-to-CMDB Synchronization Pattern

actor "Asset / Endpoint\nOwner" as AssetOwner
actor "IT Support /\nChange Manager" as ITSMUser

node "Endpoint and\nInfrastructure Fleet" as Fleet {
  component "Servers" as Servers
  component "Workstations" as Workstations
  component "Network Devices" as NetworkDevices
  component "Software\nInstallations" as Software
}

rectangle "Inventory Collection Layer" as Collection {
  component "GLPI Agent" as GLPIAgent
  component "GLPI Inventory /\nOCS-Compatible Inputs" as InventoryInputs
}

database "GLPI\nITAM + Inventory Source" as GLPI

queue "Integration Service\nScheduler + ETL + Connector" as Connector

database "Mapping and Policy Store\nCI classes, field ownership,\nlifecycle rules, identity keys" as Mapping

rectangle "Validation and\nReconciliation Gate" as Gate

database "iTop CMDB\nGoverned CIs + Relationships" as ITop

rectangle "iTop ITSM Processes" as ITSM {
  component "Incident\nManagement" as Incident
  component "Change\nManagement" as Change
  component "Service Catalog /\nImpact Analysis" as Impact
}

rectangle "Audit, Reporting, and\nException Management" as Audit

Fleet --> GLPIAgent : discovered inventory facts
Fleet --> InventoryInputs : inventory payloads
GLPIAgent --> GLPI : asset and software inventory
InventoryInputs --> GLPI : normalized inventory feed
AssetOwner --> GLPI : asset ownership, lifecycle,\nlocation, license context

GLPI --> Connector : approved asset extract\nREST API or controlled CSV export
Mapping --> Connector : mapping rules and\nfield ownership policies
Connector --> Gate : normalized CI candidate payloads
Gate --> ITop : create or update governed CIs\nREST/JSON or controlled import
Gate --> Audit : rejected records, duplicate candidates,\nmissing mandatory fields
Connector --> Audit : run metrics, errors,\ncreated/updated/skipped counts

ITop --> Incident : CI context for incidents
ITop --> Change : CI context for changes
ITop --> Impact : service relationships\nand dependency model
ITSMUser --> ITSM : triage, approve, analyze, report

note right of GLPI
Recommended role:
- ITAM source of record
- hardware/software inventory
- licenses and contracts
- asset lifecycle facts
end note

note right of ITop
Recommended role:
- governed CMDB
- CI relationships
- incident/change context
- service impact analysis
end note

note bottom of Gate
Governance controls:
1. deterministic identity matching
2. duplicate prevention
3. mandatory-field validation
4. lifecycle-state translation
5. exception queue and audit log
end note

legend right
|= Color |= Meaning |
| <#EAF3F8> | collection / process layer |
| <#FFF8E1> | system of record / database |
| <#F3E5F5> | integration service |
| <#FFFDE7> | governance note |
endlegend

@enduml

